+# Full Access & User Guide (Non-Technical)
+
+This guide explains how to open and use the full system from the UI.
+
+---
+
+## 1) URL to Open the Application
+
+### Preview URL (detected from project defaults)
+- **Frontend/UI:** `http://localhost:3000` (local preview via `npm start` in `frontend/`)
+- **Backend/API:** `http://localhost:8001`
+- **Known hosted preview reference in tests:** `https://algo-bot-validator.preview.emergentagent.com`
+
+### Deployed URL
+- No fixed production URL is configured in this repository.
+- If your team has a production deployment, use the URL from your deployment dashboard / environment config.
+
+---
+
+## 2) Access / Login
+
+- **Login required?** In current repo flow, the dashboard does **not** require an application login screen by default.
+- **Default credentials?** None configured in this repository.
+- If your org placed the app behind SSO, VPN, or a reverse proxy login, use your organization credentials.
+
+---
+
+## 3) Step-by-Step UI User Guide
+
+## A. How to run Master Pipeline
+1. Open Dashboard.
+2. Enter your strategy idea in the strategy prompt box.
+3. Select model + prop firm settings.
+4. Click **Run Full Pipeline**.
+5. Wait for pipeline completion.
+
+What happens internally:
+- generation → uniqueness/diversity filtering → real backtest → validation → correlation filter → regime adaptation → portfolio selection → risk allocation → capital scaling → cBot compile.
+
+---
+
+## B. How to read pipeline logs
+
+In the Master Pipeline tab, each stage log shows:
+- stage name
+- status icon (`[✓]` success, `[✗]` failure)
+- stage details (counts, thresholds, metrics)
+
+Important logs to look for:
+- `[✓] Correlation analysis complete`
+- `[✓] Market regime detected`
+- `[✓] Strategy selection adjusted`
+- `[✓] Portfolio selected`
+- `[✓] Risk and capital allocation complete`
+- `[✓] Capital scaling adjusted`
+
+---
+
+## C. How to understand strategy results (PF, DD, WR, Trades)
+
+- **PF (Profit Factor):** higher is better.  
+  - ~1.0 = break-even-ish
+  - >1.2 = generally acceptable
+  - >1.5 = strong
+- **DD (Drawdown %):** lower is safer.
+- **WR (Win Rate %):** percent of winning trades.
+- **Trades:** sample size. More trades = more confidence.
+
+Rule of thumb:
+- Prefer **higher PF**, **lower DD**, and **enough trades**.
+
+---
+
+## D. How to interpret portfolio output
+
+Portfolio summary combines selected strategies and shows:
+- selected count
+- deployable count
+- combined portfolio metrics
+- risk allocation output
+- market regime and regime fit indicators
+- capital scaling output (tier + scale factor)
+
+Use this to confirm:
+1. Selection is diversified
+2. Risk limits are present
+3. Capital scaling is sane (no big jumps)
+
+---
+
+## E. How to use monitoring dashboard
+
+In Master Pipeline tab → Live Performance Monitoring:
+- Click **Refresh Live**
+- Review:
+  - Portfolio health (healthy/critical)
+  - Best strategy
+  - Worst strategy
+  - Alert list
+  - Retrain logs
+
+---
+
+## F. How to trigger auto-retrain
+
+1. Open Live Performance Monitoring panel.
+2. Click **Auto-Retrain**.
+3. System will:
+   - flag underperformers,
+   - trigger retraining,
+   - replace weak strategies (with safety limits),
+   - append retrain events.
+
+---
+
+## G. How to understand alerts
+
+Common alerts:
+- **Daily loss breach**: loss exceeded configured daily cap.
+- **Strategy failure**: drawdown exceeded strategy stop threshold.
+- **Underperformance**: live PF materially below backtest baseline.
+
+When alert appears:
+1. Check strategy row details.
+2. Disable weak strategy (manual control) OR run Auto-Retrain.
+
+---
+
+## H. How capital scaling works in UI
+
+Capital scaling uses rolling performance windows:
+- last 7 days
+- last 30 days
+
+Metrics used:
+- PF
+- Drawdown
+- Win rate
+
+Scaling tiers:
+- **low_risk** (reduce capital)
+- **medium_risk** (hold baseline)
+- **high_risk** (increase capital)
+
+Safety:
+- max cap
+- min floor
+- gradual step changes only
+
+Effect:
+- updates allocated capital and max position size per strategy.
+
+---
+
+## 4) Troubleshooting (Simple)
+
+## Pipeline fails
+- Check stage logs to see the first `[✗]` stage.
+- Most common causes:
+  - missing market data
+  - missing LLM/API key
+  - compile gate failed
+
+## No strategies generated / selected
+- Try broader strategy prompt.
+- Increase `strategies_per_template`.
+- Loosen overly strict filters (correlation/risk thresholds) carefully.
+
+## Monitoring not updating
+- Ensure live trades are being ingested to backend.
+- Click **Refresh Live**.
+- Verify backend URL is correct in frontend env (`REACT_APP_BACKEND_URL`).
+
+---
+
+## Quick Start Checklist
+
+1. Open Dashboard URL
+2. Enter prompt
+3. Run Full Pipeline
+4. Review selected strategies + deployable bots
+5. Open Live Monitoring
+6. Use Auto-Retrain when alerts appear
